<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="318" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1405,2008]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1477,1503]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Etymology</emphasis>
: The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johansson" authorityYear="2021" box="[467,571,1478,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cypriotus">
<emphasis box="[467,571,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">cypriotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the 
<typeStatus box="[808,856,1478,1504]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">type</typeStatus>
locality 
<collectingCountry box="[958,1042,1477,1503]" name="Cyprus" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
, where the only known specimens were collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="318" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1405,2008]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1549,1575]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Johansson, 2021" authorityName="Johansson" authorityYear="2021" box="[448,708,1549,1575]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trochantellatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[448,708,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Ophion trochantellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[715,804,1550,1576]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but smaller, with the apical flagellomeres slenderer, the pleurosternal angles more distinct and the hind trochantelli shorter. Perhaps even more similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Szepligei, 1905" authorityName="Szepligei" authorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turcomanicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Ophion turcomanicus</emphasis>
Szépligei, 1905
</taxonomicName>
, but with more elongate flagellomeres and more prominent pleurosternal angles. Perhaps most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Shestakov, 1926)" baseAuthorityName="Shestakov" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[265,715,1657,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andalusiacus">
<emphasis box="[265,504,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Ophion andalusiacus</emphasis>
(Shestakov, 1926)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<typeStatus box="[727,825,1657,1683]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ceballos, 1940" authorityName="Ceballos" authorityYear="1940" box="[862,1193,1657,1683]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pujoli">
<emphasis box="[862,1018,1657,1683]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Ophion pujoli</emphasis>
Ceballos, 
<quantity box="[1137,1193,1657,1683]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9276" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" unit="in" value="1940.0">1940</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in MNCN examined, but with the pleurosternal angles less angulate and the posterior transverse carina of propodeum absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="319" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1405,2008]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1437,151,537]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="319" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1729,1755]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Description</emphasis>
: Male unknown. Fore wing length 
<quantity box="[743,869,1729,1756]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13‒14 mm</quantity>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[1029,1154,1729,1756]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" unit="mm" value="15.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="15.0">15‒16 mm</quantity>
. Antenna with 47 flagel- lomeres. Temple strongly buccate behind compound eyes, in lateral view about 0.9‒1.0 × as long as compound eye (
<figureCitation box="[160,265,1801,1827]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-187@18.[151,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Ophion cypriotus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM). A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, anterior view; D) head, dorsal view; E) mesopleuron, ventrolateral view; F) apical flagellomeres; G) hind trochanter and trochantellus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226054/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Fig. 12D</figureCitation>
). Malar space short, about 0.1 × as wide as mandibular base. Space between compound eye and lateral ocellus wide, about 0.3 × the diameter of ocellus. Face relatively wide (
<figureCitation box="[950,1053,1837,1863]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-187@18.[151,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Ophion cypriotus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM). A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, anterior view; D) head, dorsal view; E) mesopleuron, ventrolateral view; F) apical flagellomeres; G) hind trochanter and trochantellus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226054/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Fig. 12C</figureCitation>
). Occipital carina centrally evenly rounded. Face below antennal sockets with distinct, quite scarce punctures, the interstices between punctures about equal to their diameter. Mandibular gape acute, without internal angles, slightly worn in the known specimens (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-187@18.[151,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Ophion cypriotus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM). A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, anterior view; D) head, dorsal view; E) mesopleuron, ventrolateral view; F) apical flagellomeres; G) hind trochanter and trochantellus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226054/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Fig 12C</figureCitation>
). First flagellomere 3.5 × as long as wide. Central flagellomeres stout, about 1.5 × as long as wide. Apical flagellomeres approximately 1.7 × as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[748,850,1981,2007]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-187@18.[151,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Ophion cypriotus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM). A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, anterior view; D) head, dorsal view; E) mesopleuron, ventrolateral view; F) apical flagellomeres; G) hind trochanter and trochantellus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226054/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Fig. 12F</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum polished with weak, but quite dense punctures, space between punctures about 2.0 × their diameter. Mesopleuron shagreened mostly strongly rugulose, punctures hardly discernible. Epicnemial carina, in antero-ventral view, with pleurosternal angles prominent, right angled, anterior to sternal angles (
<figureCitation box="[538,641,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-187@18.[151,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Ophion cypriotus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM). A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, anterior view; D) head, dorsal view; E) mesopleuron, ventrolateral view; F) apical flagellomeres; G) hind trochanter and trochantellus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226054/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Fig. 12E</figureCitation>
). Scutellum without lateral carinae. Propodeum opaque with weak rugulose sculpture. Anterior transverse carina complete and two almost parallel carinae emanating from the petiolar incision present. Propodeal carinae otherwise missing (
<figureCitation box="[778,883,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-187@18.[151,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Ophion cypriotus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM). A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, anterior view; D) head, dorsal view; E) mesopleuron, ventrolateral view; F) apical flagellomeres; G) hind trochanter and trochantellus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226054/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
). Sclerotised part of first sternite ending level to spiracle. Hind trochantellus shorter than wide in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[840,944,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-187@18.[151,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Ophion cypriotus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM). A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, anterior view; D) head, dorsal view; E) mesopleuron, ventrolateral view; F) apical flagellomeres; G) hind trochanter and trochantellus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226054/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Fig. 12G</figureCitation>
). Hind femur slender, about 7.0 × as long as wide. Inner spur of hind tibia short, about 0.3 × as long as hind metatarsus. Wing membrane clear. Ramellus reaching 0.1‒0.3 × the width of the discosubmarginal cell. Radius very weakly sinuous, almost straight before junction with pterostigma. Nervellus broken in the middle by the discoidella.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">
<emphasis box="[199,336,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Colouration</emphasis>
: Body light orange with extensive yellow markings typical of steppe or desert species (
<figureCitation box="[1319,1424,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-187@18.[151,1436,561,1800]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Ophion cypriotus sp. nov. holotype female (OÖLM). A) Habitus, lateral view; B) scutellum and propodeum, dorsal view; C) head, anterior view; D) head, dorsal view; E) mesopleuron, ventrolateral view; F) apical flagellomeres; G) hind trochanter and trochantellus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226054/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor sheath testaceous. Mandibular teeth black.
</paragraph>
